  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study aims to investigate the prevalence of genetic polymorphisms in adults with iron
      deficiency and anemia, and the responses to two different treatments: iron sulphate and a
      composite herbal medicine (Hibiscus sabdariffa plus Centella asiatica). The main outcome will
      be hemoglobin, measured before and after 6 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
